In a new chapter of her memoir, Hard Choices , Hillary Clinton said she was 'unabashedly giddy' when her daughter Chelsea gave birth to Charlotte last year . 
  She said she and her husband Bill 'whooped' for joy at the birth of their first grandchild but that Chelsea was more organized and relaxed than she was . 
  She revealed that she saw tears in her husband's eyes after the birth . 
  The former Secretary of State said the birth has motivated her to run for president . 
  She is expected to announce her plans on Sunday . 
 